b'II. How to Apply'
b'A. Admission Requirements'
b'MS Thesis/ Course- Work Only'
b'Applications for admission are individually evaluated by the Graduate Admissions Committee. A complete set of transcripts of all undergraduate and graduate work is required before an application is evaluated for admission. In addition to the application requirements of the Office of Admissions and the policies set by the Graduate College, applicants should meet program requirements for admission. Meeting minimum requirements does not, however, guarantee admission. Program requirements are given below: Baccalaureate Field:\xc2\xa0'
b'Electrical or computer engineering, or other closely related curriculum.'
b'Grade Point Average:'
b'At least 3.00/4.00 for the final 60 semester hours (90 quarter hours) of undergraduate study is expected.'
b'Tests Required:'
b'All international applicants should report general test scores of GRE. Applicants with a bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree from an accredited U.S. institution are not required to provide GRE scores; however, GRE scores may improve prospects for financial aid.'
b'Minimum English Competency Test Score: TOEFL:'
b'590 (paper-based); 80, with subscores of Reading 19, Listening 17, Speaking 20, and Writing 21 (iBT Internet-based), OR,'
b'IELTS:'
b'6.5, with subscores of 6.0 for all four subscores, OR,'
b'PTE-Academic:'
b'54, with subscores of Reading 51, Listening 47, Speaking 53, and Writing 56.'
b'Letters of Recommendation:'
b'Not required for admission unless specifically requested by the Graduate Admissions Committee after reviewing academic and other credentials.'
b'Personal Statement:'
b'Not required.'
b'PhD'
b'Applications for admission are individually evaluated by the Graduate Admissions Committee. A complete set of transcripts of all undergraduate and graduate work is required before an application is evaluated for admission. In addition to the application requirements of the Office of Admissions and the policies set by the Graduate College, applicants should meet program requirements for admission. Meeting minimum requirements does not, however, guarantee admission. Program requirements are given below: Doctor of Philosophy Prior Degrees:'
b'Applicants must have a bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s or master\xe2\x80\x99s degree in electrical engineering or computer engineering or a related field. Applicants with a bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree and an outstanding academic record are encouraged to seek admission directly to the PhD program.'
b'Grade Point Average:'
b'At least 3.50/4.00.'
b'Tests Required:'
b'All international applicants should report general test scores of GRE. Applicants with a bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree from an accredited U.S. institution are not required to provide GRE scores; however, GRE scores may improve prospects for financial aid. Graduates of non-English-speaking countries who seek appointment as Teaching Assistants are encouraged to submit a TSE score (minimum acceptable score is 50).'
b'Minimum English Competency Test Score: TOEFL:'
b'590 (paper-based); 80, with subscores of Reading 19, Listening 17, Speaking 20, and Writing 21 (iBT Internet-based), OR,'
b'IELTS:'
b'6.5, with subscores of 6.0 for all four subscores, OR,'
b'PTE-Academic:'
b'54, with subscores of Reading 51, Listening 47, Speaking 53, and Writing 56.'
b'Letters of Recommendation:'
b'Three required.'
b'Personal Statement:'
b'Not required.'
b'Other Requirements:'
b'No limited-status admissions.'
b'B. Application Deadline The application deadlines are set by the Graduate College: Click here to see the deadlines. It is recommended that all application materials should be submitted by January 15 for admission in Fall semester of that year in order to get full consideration for financial aid. University fellowship\xc2\xa0nominations are due by the end of January and department financial aid decisions (TA/RA/TFW) are made about the middle of February to the middle of March. C. Graduate Admissions'
b'Click here to see the deadlines'
